Author-Name:    Domberger, Simon
Title:   Relative Price Variability and Inflation: A Disaggregated Analysis. 
Journal: Journal of Political Economy
Pages: 547-66
Issue: 3
Volume: 95
Year: 1987
Month:  June 
Abstract:
  Relative price variability has been studied at the cross-sectional
 (intermarket) level. This paper addresses the equally important phenomenon
 of intramarket variability: the dispersion of commodity price movements
 around the industry average. Using quarterly price data for eighty
 disaggregated commodity groups in the United Kingdom from 1974 to 1984,
 the paper investigates the determinants of intramarket price variability
 and replicates some previous cross-sectional tests for the United Kingdom.
 Intramarket price variability is found to be positively related to
 inflation. Intramarket variability is found to be positively related to
 the average (market) rate of price change.  Copyright 1987 by University of Chicago Press.
